akrotiri (greek: ακρωτήρι, literally "promontory") is a peninsula and former municipality in the chania regional unit, crete, greece. since the 2011 local government reform it is part of the municipality chania, of which it is a municipal unit. its ancient name was kiamon while the byzantines called it charaka. the seat of akrotiri municipality was pythari. stavros became famous because of the film zorba the greek.